Step1: Create the new Environment using Anaconda Prompt
            conda create -n env_name python==3.6.9 (mentioning a python version is optional
                                                but always a good practice)
       Activate new Environment:
            conda activate env_name
       To check the list of Environments:
            conda env list

Step2: Go to Python Interpreter (File>Settings>Project  or search for python Interpreter
       Go to settings in Python Interpreter > Click Add
       Copy the environment address from 'conda env list' command on anaconda prompt
       paste it here in Pycharm after clicking Add above.